Kitui Senator David Musila has accused Governor Julius Malombe of using his staff, including ward administrators and executives, to campaign and dish out money to woo voters to support him.He said Malombe is also accusing him of irregularities. They are both seeking the Wiper ticket to run for Kitui governor. The party primaries were held on Monday but results are yet to be announced."I'm not using my party position as Wiper chairman to cause a disturbance in the nominations. I'm strictly focused on winning," Musila said.He spoke at AIC Migwani Primary School on Monday.Musila urged Malombe to support him if he wins.Malombe said there is a local radio station being used to spread rumours that he is using county resources and staff to campaign for his reelection.